quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  22,16,"Thus We have sent it (the Quran) down as clear verses. Allah (God) guides anyone He wants to."
  22,17,"Allah (God) will sort out those who believe, as well as those who have become Jews, Sabeans, Christians, Magians, and those who associate [others with Him], on Resurrection Day. Allah (God) is a Witness for everything."
  22,18,"Have you not seen how whoever is in Heaven and whoever is on earth drops down on his knees before Allah (God), as well as the sun, moon and stars, the mountains, trees and animals, and many people, and many [of those] are deserving torment. Anyone whom Allah (God) disgraces will have no one to honor him. Allah (God) does anything He wishes."
  22,19,"Both [sets of] these opponents debate about their Lord. Those who disbelieve will have garments tailored out of fire for them; over their heads scalding water will be poured."
  22,20,"Anything in their stomachs as well as their skins will be melted by it."
  22,21,"They (Hell guards) will have iron goads [to retrain them]:"
  22,22,"every time they may want to leave because of [their] gloom, they will be sent back to it: "Taste the torment of burning!""
  22,23,"Allah (God) will admit those who believe and perform honorable deeds into gardens through which rivers flow; there they will be decked out with gold and pearl bracelets while their clothing will be [made of] silk."